.TH "RTCINBOUNDRTPSTREAMSTATS.BYTESRECEIVED" "3JS" "October 31, 2025" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
RTCInboundRtpStreamStats.bytesReceived \- RTCInboundRtpStreamStats:
bytesReceived property
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]bytesReceived\f[B]\f[R] property of the
\f[CR]RTCInboundRtpStreamStats\f[R] dictionary indicates the total
number of bytes received so far from this synchronization source (SSRC),
not including header and padding bytes.
.PP
The value can be used to calculate an approximation of the average media
data rate:
.IP
.EX
avgDataRate = rtcInboundRtpStreamStats.bytesReceived / elapsedTime;
.EE
.PP
The property value is reset to zero if the sender\(cqs SSRC identifier
changes for any reason.
.SH VALUE
A positive integer.
